{
  "stem": "9725.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remember for instance, one time-- that was in another camp, but not in Bolkenhain, but Bolkenhain-- you know, [GERMAN] had three camps, and I was in all three of them.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this particular thing happened in another camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were standing in the enclosure.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were not with Frau Kugler anymore at that point.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But you had to stand appell, you know, roll call, for a very long time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And suddenly bread sailed over the barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we knew who threw the bread, and we knew who had it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And everybody was beaten that day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nobody would give the girl away who, who had the bread.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, this was the sort of thing, you know?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In Bolkenhain, were you able to do anything?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What did you girls do when you had any free time?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We didn't have an awful lot of free time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But when we did, I know people would-- I wrote a play.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a Hanukkah play, and that's something that is still very important to me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My friend Ilse and I played two grandmothers in that play.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we predicted, of course, a brilliant future for everyone.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The stage was on a clearing between the bunks on the one-legged [? bob. ?] Then our two granddaughters came and listened to us for a while.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then in a loud stage whisper they said, come let's talk about our boyfriends.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know how old people exaggerate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so we were 16 and 18 at that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We seemed to have caught the very core of our hope that one day we live in a world where Jewish grandmothers will live and Jewish grandchildren will live.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But best of all, our grandchildren will not believe our tales of the past.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
